# subagent invocations — append-only telemetry log
#
# Format: TAB-separated. One row per invocation.
#   <ISO-8601 timestamp>\t<subagent-name>\t<spawning-context>\t<agent_id>\t<parent_id>\t<duration_ms>\t<outcome>\t<tool_calls>
#
# Older rows may have fewer columns — the architect parser reads what's there.
#
# spawning-context examples:
#   "parent: post-claim verification on /surveys"
#   "manual: Romit invoked for architecture audit"
#   "pre-commit hook: discipline-log growth trigger"
#
# Lines beginning with '#' are comments and ignored by the architect parser.
